node.title: JPMorgan says Tesla owes it $162 million because of an Elon Musk tweet.
node.description: The tweet, in which Mr. Musk claimed he had secured funding to take Tesla private, initially sent the automaker’s shares soaring. But they sank when it quickly became clear that no such deal had been reached.

node.title: 'It's going to be bad news': Neighbours brace for tragic outcome to Tyrrell investigation

node.title: NZ sees record community cases, threats prompt more security for MPs
